This paper deals with resource allocation in wireless networks, specifically LTE-U networks coexisting with other wireless networks. The paper discusses the use of carrier aggregation to integrate licensed and unlicensed bands to enhance transmission capacity. The problem is formulated as a multi-objective optimization problem, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes a matching framework, which could fall under categories such as cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses fairness among users of different radio access networks, which could suggest a category such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
